# UI/UX Consistency Standards

## Design System
- Use consistent color palette: `#0A4056` (primary), `#107EAA` (accent)
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind classes
- Use consistent typography and font weights
- Implement consistent button styles and hover states

## Component Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Follow consistent class ordering: layout, spacing, colors, typography
- Use consistent border radius and shadows
- Implement proper focus states for accessibility

## Form Design
- Use consistent form field styling
- Implement proper validation feedback
- Use consistent button styles for actions
- Maintain proper spacing between form elements

## Modal Patterns
- Use consistent modal backdrop and positioning
- Implement proper close button placement
- Use consistent modal header styling
- Maintain proper form layout within modals

## Table Design
- Use consistent table styling with proper borders
- Implement hover states for interactive rows
- Use consistent action button styling
- Maintain proper spacing and alignment

## Example Styling Patterns
```tsx
// Button styling
className="bg-[#107EAA] text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-[#0e6b8f] cursor-pointer"

// Form input styling
className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#107EAA]"

// Modal backdrop
className="fixed inset-0 bg-black bg-opacity-50 flex items-center justify-center z-50"
```